            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "The Contoso Electronics Whistleblower Policy is designed to foster a transparent and ethical workplace. It encourages employees, contractors, and third parties to report unethical, illegal activities, or violations of company policy. Key points include:\n\n1. **Definition of Whistleblower**: An individual reporting activities deemed illegal, unethical, or inconsistent with company policy.\n   \n2. **Reporting Procedures**: Reports can be made by:\n   - Contacting the Human Resources Department.\n   - Emailing the Compliance Officer at compliance@contoso.com.\n   - Calling the Compliance Hotline at 1-800-555-1212.\n   Employees can also report anonymously via the hotline.\n\n3. **Retaliation Prohibited**: Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited, with disciplinary actions taken against violators.\n\n4. **Confidentiality**: Whistleblower identities are protected to the extent permitted by law.\n\n5. **Investigation**: All reports are promptly and thoroughly investigated.\n\nThis policy supports employees in maintaining ethical practices and addressing concerns safely.",
